Parliament, Friday, 22 June 2018 – The Portfolio Committee on Rural Development and Land Reform will today hold the last public hearings session in Mpumalanga on the Restitution of Land Rights Amendment Bill. The aim of the Bill is to amongst others, to develop and keep a National Land Restitution Register as well as to provide for the re-opening of the second phase to lodge land claims through the restitution process. Details of the Public hearings Date: Friday, 22 June 2018
	Venue: Elukwatini Community Hall, Elukwatini
	Time: 09:30am ISSUED BY THE PARLIAMENTARY COMMUNICATION SERVICES ON BEHALF OF THE CHAIRPERSON OF THE PORTFOLIO COMMITTEE ON RURAL DEVELOPMEN AND LAND REFORM, MS PHUMUZILE NGWENYA-MABILA For media enquiries or interviews with the Chairperson, please contact the Committee’s Media Officer: Name: Malatswa Molepo (Mr)
	Parliamentary Communication Services
